Detailed Description

cvmx_gmx::_rx::_frm_ctl

GMX_RX_FRM_CTL = Frame Control

Notes: * PRE_STRP When PRE_CHK is set (indicating that the PREAMBLE will be sent), PRE_STRP determines if the PREAMBLE+SFD bytes are thrown away or sent to the Octane core as part of the packet.

In either mode, the PREAMBLE+SFD bytes are not counted toward the packet size when checking against the MIN and MAX bounds. Furthermore, the bytes are skipped when locating the start of the L2 header for DMAC and Control frame recognition.

* CTL_BCK/CTL_DRP These bits control how the HW handles incoming PAUSE packets. Here are the most common modes of operation: CTL_BCK=1,CTL_DRP=1 - HW does it all CTL_BCK=0,CTL_DRP=0 - SW sees all pause frames CTL_BCK=0,CTL_DRP=1 - all pause frames are completely ignored

These control bits should be set to CTL_BCK=0,CTL_DRP=0 in halfdup mode. Since PAUSE packets only apply to fulldup operation, any PAUSE packet would constitute an exception which should be handled by the processing cores. PAUSE packets should not be forwarded.
